history.content:
I would not say it's safe to wait until phase 2 to enroll into CS 189 if you really want/need the class. Our budget constraints are such that you cannot count on the class expanding so even if the waitlist is re-prioritized (which there is no guarantee it will be), you very likely won't get in if you wait to join the waitlist.

Remember, we use reserved seating to indicate which students are get priority access. How you spend your phase 1 units indicates which classes are most important to you.

https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#upper

Yesterday there were more than 100 seats available for CS 189, so I thought it would be safe to phase 2. Today there are only a handful of seats left.
